Another archaeological source is the {{ill|Inaridai Sword|lt="Gift of Wang"|ja|鉄剣・鉄刀銘文|qq=draft|qq=draft}} excavated from the {{ill|Inaridai Kofun Group|ja|稲荷台1号墳}} (Ichihara City, Chiba Prefecture). (or Chin), since he is self-explanatory only by writing "Wang".{{Sfn|Mori Kosho|2010|pp=51-55}}{{Sfn|Kouchi Haruhito|2018|pp=73-119}} It should be noted, however, that the [[Inariyama Sword|iron sword from Inariyama Kofun]] inscription and the {{ill|Eta Funayama Sword|lt=iron sword from Etafuneyama Kofun|ja|鉄剣・鉄刀銘文|qq=draft|qq=draft}} inscription are distinct from the "Great King" of the [[Inariyama Sword]]{{Sfn|河内春人|2018|pp=73-119}}。

